(42, 9, 61, 5, 33, 9, 9, 'bid them farewell', 'Family and Commitment to God', 'This connection highlights the theme of prioritizing commitment to God over familial ties. Both passages emphasize the tension between following God''s call and acknowledging family obligations.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 61, 21, 9, 10, 10, NULL, 'Urgency of Action', 'This connection highlights the urgency of taking action in life. In Luke 9:61, the desire to delay following Jesus contrasts with Ecclesiastes 9:10''s call to do work with might while one is alive.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 62, 50, 3, 13, 13, 'looking back', 'Focus on the Future', 'This connection highlights the importance of not looking back while pursuing one''s spiritual journey. Both passages emphasize the need to forget past distractions and focus on what lies ahead.', 'theme', 0.9019999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 62, 58, 10, 38, 38, NULL, 'Faithfulness and Commitment', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not looking back or drawing back in one''s commitment to God. They highlight that faithfulness is essential for those who seek to be part of the kingdom of God.', 'theme', 0.762, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 62, 61, 2, 20, 22, 'fit for the kingdom of God', 'Commitment to Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of steadfastness in faith. Luke 9:62 warns against looking back after committing to the kingdom, while 2 Peter 2:20-22 highlights the dangers of returning to former ways after knowing righteousness.', 'theme', 0.6499999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 62, 42, 17, 31, 32, 'looking back', 'Urgency in Following Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of not looking back when following Jesus. The call to not return back in Luke 17:31-32 parallels the idea of being unfit for the kingdom if one looks back in Luke 9:62.', 'theme', 0.608, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 62, 59, 1, 6, 8, 'looking back', 'Faith and Commitment in Discipleship', 'This connection highlights the importance of unwavering commitment in following Jesus. Both passages emphasize the need to avoid looking back or wavering in faith to be fit for God''s kingdom.', 'theme', 0.5449999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 62, 19, 78, 8, 9, NULL, 'Turning Back in Faithfulness', 'This connection highlights the theme of turning back as a sign of unfitness for God''s purposes. Both passages emphasize the consequences of looking back or turning away during critical moments of commitment.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 9, 62, 44, 15, 37, 38, 'looking back', 'Commitment to the Mission', 'This connection highlights the theme of commitment in both passages. In Luke, Jesus emphasizes the necessity of not looking back once one has committed to the work of the kingdom, while in Acts, Paul''s reluctance to take John Mark reflects concerns about commitment to their mission.', 'theme', 0.426, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 1, 41, 6, 7, 13, 'sent them two and two', 'Sending of Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize the sending of disciples in pairs to preach and heal. They highlight the authority given to the disciples and the instructions for their journey.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 1, 42, 9, 52, 52, 'sent them two and two before his face', 'Preparation for Jesus'' Arrival', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of sending messengers to prepare for Jesus'' arrival. In Luke 9:52, messengers are sent to a Samaritan village, while in Luke 10:1, the seventy are sent ahead into various cities.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 1, 40, 10, 1, 4, 'sent them two and two', 'Sending of Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize the appointment and sending of disciples by Jesus. Luke 10:1 mentions sending ''other seventy'' while Matthew 10:1 refers to the calling of ''the twelve disciples,'' highlighting the theme of Jesus empowering his followers for ministry.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 1, 4, 11, 24, 26, 'the Lord appointed other seventy also', 'Seventy Sent Forth', 'This connection highlights the appointment of seventy individuals in both passages. In Luke, the Lord sends seventy disciples ahead of Him, paralleling Moses gathering seventy elders to receive the Spirit in Numbers.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 1, 42, 3, 4, 6, 'sent them two and two before his face', 'Preparation for the Lord''s Coming', 'This connection highlights the theme of preparation for the Lord''s arrival. In both passages, there is an emphasis on sending forth messengers to prepare the way for Jesus, indicating the importance of readiness for His ministry.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 1, 4, 11, 16, 16, 'seventy', 'Seventy Sent Forth', 'This connection highlights the appointment of seventy individuals in both passages. In Luke, the Lord sends out seventy disciples, paralleling the gathering of seventy elders in Numbers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 1, 44, 13, 2, 4, 'sent them two and two', 'Sending of Messengers', 'Both passages emphasize the act of sending individuals for a specific mission. In Luke, the Lord sends the seventy ahead of Him, while in Acts, the Holy Ghost sends Barnabas and Saul for their work.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 2, 40, 9, 36, 38, 'the harvest truly is great, but the labourers are few', 'Connection of Harvest and Laborers', 'Both passages emphasize the great need for laborers in the harvest. They share the same phrasing about the harvest being plenteous and the laborers being few, highlighting the urgency of prayer for more workers.', 'theme', 0.58, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 2, 43, 4, 35, 38, 'the harvest truly is great', 'Connection of Harvest Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the urgency of the harvest and the need for laborers. Luke 10:2 speaks of the great harvest and few laborers, while John 4:35-38 highlights that the fields are already white for harvest, indicating readiness. This connection highlights the call to action for laborers in God''s work.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 2, 46, 3, 6, 9, 'labourers into his harvest', 'Laborers in God''s Harvest', 'Both passages emphasize the role of laborers in God''s work. Luke highlights the need for laborers in the harvest, while 1 Corinthians speaks of those who plant and water, underscoring their collective effort in God''s mission.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 2, 41, 16, 15, 15, 'the harvest truly is great', 'Call to Evangelism', 'Both passages emphasize the need for laborers to spread the gospel. Luke highlights the urgency of the harvest, while Mark commands the disciples to go and preach to all. This connection highlights the call for active participation in sharing the message.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 2, 52, 5, 12, 12, 'labourers', 'Laborers in the Harvest', 'This connection highlights the theme of laborers in both passages. Luke emphasizes the need for laborers in the harvest, while 1 Thessalonians calls for recognition of those who labor among the community.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 2, 53, 3, 1, 1, 'pray ye therefore the Lord of the harvest', 'Prayer for Laborers and Word', 'This connection highlights the theme of prayer for the advancement of God''s work. Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer in sending forth laborers and allowing the word of the Lord to spread.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 2, 40, 20, 1, 1, 'labourers', 'Connection of Labourers in Harvest', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''labourers'' in relation to a harvest or vineyard. Luke 10:2 speaks of the need for labourers in the harvest, while Matthew 20:1 describes a householder hiring labourers for his vineyard, highlighting the importance of work in God''s kingdom.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 3, 40, 10, 16, 16, 'lambs among wolves', 'Connection of Sheep and Wolves', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of being sent as sheep or lambs among wolves, highlighting the vulnerability of the disciples in a hostile environment. This connection underscores the need for wisdom and innocence in their mission.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 3, 44, 20, 29, 29, 'wolves', 'Wolves and the Flock', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of ''wolves'' as a threat to the vulnerable. Luke describes the disciples as ''lambs among wolves,'' while Acts warns of ''grievous wolves'' entering the flock.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 3, 26, 2, 3, 6, 'I send you forth as lambs', 'Sending of Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being sent into hostile environments. Luke speaks of being sent as ''lambs among wolves,'' while Ezekiel describes being sent to a ''rebellious house'' and encourages not to fear their opposition.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 3, 43, 15, 20, 20, 'lambs among wolves', 'Persecution of Followers', 'Both passages emphasize the vulnerability of believers. ''Lambs among wolves'' suggests danger, while ''persecuted me'' indicates that followers will face similar threats.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 3, 40, 10, 22, 22, 'lambs among wolves', 'Endurance Amidst Opposition', 'Both passages emphasize the challenges faced by believers. Luke 10:3 describes being sent as ''lambs among wolves,'' while Matthew 10:22 speaks of being ''hated of all men.'' This connection highlights the theme of perseverance in the face of hostility.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 3, 43, 10, 12, 12, 'lambs among wolves', 'Sheep and Wolves Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the danger posed by wolves to sheep. Luke 10:3 presents the disciples as lambs among wolves, while John 10:12 describes the wolf''s threat to the sheep, highlighting the need for protection.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 10, 3, 36, 3, 3, 3, 'lambs among wolves', 'Lambs and Wolves Imagery', 'This connection highlights the imagery of vulnerability and danger, as both passages depict the presence of wolves in a threatening context. Luke emphasizes the disciples'' role as lambs among wolves, while Zephaniah describes judges as evening wolves, suggesting a predatory nature.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
